        \item \textit{Relevance:} A foundational textbook on the mathematics of finance, providing the rigorous theoretical background for the time value of money and annuity formulas.
    \end{itemize}
    
    \item \textbf{Fabozzi, F. J. (2015). \textit{Bond Markets, Analysis, and Strategies} (9th ed.). Pearson.}
    \begin{itemize}
        \item \textit{Relevance:} Contains excellent sections on amortization and the mathematics of fixed-income securities, directly applicable to loans.
    \end{itemize}
    
    \item \textbf{Investopedia. (n.d.). \textit{Amortization Calculator \& Formula}.}
    \begin{itemize}
        \item \textit{Relevance:} Provides a clear, accessible explanation of the concepts and common industry practices. (I will seek additional peer-reviewed sources for the final report).
    \end{itemize}
\end{enumerate}

